<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's a reality television personality best known for being in the girl group Danity Kane, and now frequently posts sponsored content on Instagram. </p>

<p>But on Sunday, Aubrey O'Day was pictured looking remarkably different from how she appears on social media, as she took her two dogs for a quiet stroll in Palm Springs, California. </p>

<p>The sighting comes just a week after the 36-year-old star posted an advertisement for the Flat Tummy App on her Instagram account that showed her in a revealing swimsuit, though it appears to have been heavily airbrushed.  </p>

<p>PICTURED: Aubrey O'Day looks unrecognizable as she emerges for a quiet stroll with her dogs on Sunday in Palm Springs, California… 16 years after finding fame as a pop star in Danity Kane</p>

<p>Sponsored post: Aubrey posted this snap of herself looking trim in a swimsuit as she advertised the Flat Tummy App on August 20</p>

<p>'Can't wait to see the progress as I continue the workouts,' Aubrey captioned the snap from August 20, which she posted to her 936,000 followers. </p>

<p>She added: 'Nothing beats a poolside workout, and with my new <?php echo e('@'); ?>flattummyapp I can do my workout anywhere, anytime.' </p>

<p>The star - who has appeared in both Celebrity Apprentice and Celebrity Big Brother - has posted a series of bikini shots on social media over the last few months, though it is not clear when the pictures were taken. </p>

<p>On July 15, she posted a string of bikini shots, wearing Rihanna's Savage X Fenty line and made sure to tag the brand in her post. </p>

<p>Difference: Aubrey was last pictured at an event in October last year (left) at the premiere of Marriage Boot Camp in Los Angeles</p>

<p>Pampered pooches: Aubrey is known for her love of dogs, and getting her pets' fur colored</p>

<p>Making an impact: The singer and reality star got herself known for her daring red carpet looks, like this look (right) from 2012 in Las Vegas </p>

<p>Aubrey is still an active member of the band Danity Kane, which now appears to be a duo, having reunited for a second time as a trio in 2018. </p>

<p>Along with singer Dawn Richard, the pair released the electronic single New Kings earlier this year in March. </p>

<p>She has also been posting videos of fans dancing to their new music on her Instagram account. </p>

<p>Inking: This Instagram snap - posted in January this year - shows a very recognizable tattoo </p>

<p>Rib: Aubrey was seen showing off her unmistakable tattoos while out and about</p>

<p>Stamped: Aubrey has previously showed off her bar code neck tattoo... which was clearly visible as she stepped out with her dogs</p>

<p>Last week, Aubrey posted a tribute to her beloved pooches on Twitter for National Dog Day, showing off their multicolored fur. </p>

<p>Fans have speculated about her changing looks over the years, but in an interview Aubrey admitted that she knows 'all the tricks' when it comes to making your appearance seem different. </p>

<p>'I've had lip fillers and Botox. I put a lot of filters,' she told UsWeekly just last year, adding: 'I know all the tricks and I use them.' </p>

